## 2Â Â KQL PerformanceÂ Tuning

| Technique             | Snippet                                           | Typical Gain                                                   |                                        |                         |             |                |
| --------------------- | ------------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------- | ----------------------- | ----------- | -------------- |
| Time filter first     | \`                                                | where TimeGenerated >= startTime and TimeGenerated < endTime\` | Â 20â€‘30â€¯%                               |                         |             |                |
| Materialised baseline | `let _baseline = materialize(...);`               | Â avoids NÃ— recompute                                           |                                        |                         |             |                |
| `serialize`Â +Â `lag()` | \`                                                | serialize                                                      | extend PrevTime = lag(TimeGenerated)\` | Â less CPU thanÂ `prev()` |             |                |
| Composite join key    | \`extend JoinKey = hash\_sha256(UserPrincipalName |                                                                | IPAddress                              |                         | DeviceId)\` | Â quicker joins |

#### Dynamic Risk Percentile Example

```kql
let p80 = toscalar(SigninLogs | summarize percentiles(TotalRiskScore, 80));
| extend RiskLevel = iff(TotalRiskScore >= p80, "High", "Normal")
```

